{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"BRAINSTORM DECISION (AC #1) — option (b)/hybrid: COMPLETION-AWARE container plan-review.\n\nChosen over (a) exempt-epics (throws away the container security review ADR 0016 added) and over a\nfreshness-axis redesign (rejected: code-drift invalidation is INTENTIONAL — a container's plan is\nreviewed against codebase state; e.g. G6 runs at container scope). This epic changes only what a\nlegitimately re-fired review DOES, not when it fires.\n\nRe-fire triggers are legitimate + infrequent: a paused epic reopened (ADR 0009), or a material\ncourse-correction to the epic plan (material-fingerprint). The claim cascade is NOT a driver — it\nonly fires while the parent is `open`, so an in_progress epic does not re-gate on further child\nclaims (`_resolve_open_parent` returns None for a non-open parent).\n\nDesign: a deterministic Pass-3 \"completion floor\" (third floor beside novelty ADR 0008 + drift-\nrefresh ADR 0002), fed by a SEPARATE `plan_review_completion` Pass-2 sub-call (mirrors\n`plan_review_novelty`) answering three atomic orthogonal sub-questions per finding —\nATTRIBUTION (which closed child; structural for G3/G4 via `_container_child`), CONTAINMENT (limited\nto that child vs spans an open sibling/system), LAYER (plan-semantics vs delivered-functionality).\nDrop iff ALL: attribution=DELIVERED-NOW child (valid completion attestation via validity-on-read,\nOR superseded by an in-epic sibling) AND containment=limited AND layer=plan-semantics AND\npriority<floor AND criterion NOT in {security,contract}. Every ambiguous answer\n(insufficient/n/a/spans-open/delivered-functionality) fails toward KEEP; drops go to the\nREVIEW_RESULT sidecar and are recomputed each run.\n\nKEY EDGE DECISIONS: in-progress children stay FULLY in scope (v1); force-close is NEVER trusted as\ndelivered (closes the force-close laundering hole); abandoned children stay in scope (a real plan\nhole to surface); superseded-by-in-epic-sibling IS treated as delivered-elsewhere (prevents the\nstale-closed-ticket hard-block Joe has observed). DEFERRED (separate epics): partial-completion\nattestation for in-progress children; a structured `resolution` enum on `close`; the sidecar\nre-injection queue; an optional second LAYER binary (calibration-gated).\n\nGrounding: Tricorder/SonarQube/GitHub code-scanning (suppress on delivered+below-severity+\nnon-actionable, severity/security hard veto, never attribution-alone, never deletion); G-Eval/\nCheckList/FLASK (few frozen atomic binaries + deterministic aggregation); ODC + IEEE-1028 (once\ndelivered, governing review shifts plan-review -> code-review; plan-semantics feedback goes moot,\ndelivered-substance stays live). Full trail in the session log."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782973212378300001,"uuid":"74eb956f-4c95-4d92-bf95-8c2a31d674a9"}